<text>
    <group>
       
    
    <!-- type is letter -->

    
        
        <pb n="6501" facs="#L1916_2347_img_6501"/>
            <text type="letter" decls="#corresp1">
                <body>
                    

<opener><dateline><date>Aug 25</date></dateline></opener>
<lb/>and the dirge of 
<lb/><unclear>Colquoolan</unclear> (??) you
<lb/> will love my spelling
<lb/>of this! I expect it 
<lb/>must be one of the 
<lb/>Artists rifles who form
<lb/>the body guard here
<lb/>a safe but not very
<lb/>glorious role.</p>
<p>I wish K would
<lb/>let me know what
<lb/>he thinks of the dispatch
<lb/>up to date. I must
<lb/>go and see him tomorrow
<lb/>to know how I am to
        
    

    
         
        <pb n="6502" facs="#L1916_2347_img_6502"/>
        
        
           
            <lb/>deal with a fortnights
<lb/>almost uninterrupted
<lb/>failures at the end
<lb/> of July! Things are
<lb/>better again now, &amp; will
<lb/> be easier but not
<lb/>the intermediate period.</p>
<p>I don't want long
<lb/>letters now old thing
<lb/>nor to give you anymore
<lb/>business. Please look
<lb/>after yourself as your
<lb/>payment of the many 
<lb/>good marks you owe
<lb/> &#x2014; you say &#x2014; to your 
<lb/>bw.</p> 
<signed>WB Spender</signed>
        
    
         
        <pb n="6507" facs="#L1916_2347_img_6507"/>
        
        
           
            <lb/>on leave and do it there tho' I see <add>there would be</add> difficulties 
<lb/>about maps, of which I have several square
<lb/>yards for each day of the month to look
<lb/>at! </p>
<p>Yesterday someone came in for a <unclear>break</unclear>
<lb/>said he came from Fermanagh talked of gun
<lb/> running, and Fermanagh but I could not place
<lb/>him even when he said something which showed
<lb/>his brother had died &amp; been a peer. Very interesting
<lb/>it was but I wish I had known before he left
<lb/>that it was Crichton &#x2014; who is now a King's 
<lb/>messenger and whom I hope to see out here
<lb/>again.</p>
<p>Several times at night I have been 
<lb/>startled by someone who whistles some of 
<lb/> my special tunes &#x2014; Autumn the apple blossom
        
    
         
        <pb n="6508" facs="#L1916_2347_img_6508"/>
        
        
           
            <p>I haven't yet appeared in the Gazette &#x2014; an 
<lb/>unusually long wait! Supposing I am sent 
<lb/>back to Capt again what a bw and pr we shall be
<lb/> it will be a case of pppr! I hope my exalted 
<lb/>encomium &#x2014; shan't talk of pay now! &#x2014; begins
<lb/> from the date of my duties, an extra 9/- a day
<lb/>I believe I get which ought to pay for a 
<lb/> pr's chocolate even on a holiday!</p>
<p>I resubmitted the dispatch 19 May to
<lb/>16 July to K today but I shall not hear what 
<lb/>he thinks for a day or two, &amp; shall be very
<lb/>depressed in consequence I expect for I really
<lb/> have tried hard, &amp; only want a pr to make
<lb/> it quite a success. I wish I could take it home
        
    
         
        <pb n="6511" facs="#L1916_2347_img_6511"/>
        
        
           
            <date>August 25th <del>July</del></date>
<salute>My pr</salute>
<p>Got your letter of 22nd this evening<add><hi rend="superscript">24th</hi></add>. No
<lb/> old thing it won't do. If you aren't feeling better
<lb/> when you get this &amp; tell me so I shall write to 
<lb/>Lady R &amp; tell her she must get someone to
<lb/> take on from the first week in September.</p>
<p>I have written to <unclear>Rex</unclear> and told him <unclear>Jin</unclear>
<lb/>will manage <del>your</del> his parcels and we will settle
<lb/> up with her.</p>
<p>In your next letter tell me how you stand
<lb/>in regard to our business and do no more. I
<lb/>can arrange nearly everything with Maguire
<lb/>from here. <unclear>The lending</unclear> to the Government is
<lb/>rather urgent though as I believe it has to be done
        
    
         
        <pb n="6512" facs="#L1916_2347_img_6512"/>
        
        
           
            <lb/>by the 1 Sept so I enclose a letter to Mr
<lb/>Maguire for you to forward if you have not 
<lb/>already <del>done</del> written.</p>
<p>But the first thing is your holiday
<lb/>&amp; I tell you flat I shall write to Ruby
<lb/>&amp; have you sacked if you are not very
<lb/>good!  I am thinking of asking Jessie to
<lb/> vet you but hitherto I have been able to
<lb/> trust my pr to tell me the truth of how
<lb/>she feels and so won't take extreme measures yet.</p>
<p>As for your holiday you need not go
<lb/>on economical lines this time as I want it 
<lb/>to be a real holiday.</p>
        
    
                </body>
            </text>

        
            
        
            
        
            
        
            
        
            
        
            
        

         

